   <concept id="FAR_23_304" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">23.304</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li " props="Runin">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1550e12">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1550e17">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              href="52.223-3.dita#FAR_52_223_3"
                              base="FAR-52.223-3"
                              xtrc="52.223-3"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>, Hazardous Material Identification and Material Safety Data, in solicitations and contracts if the contract will require the delivery of hazardous materials as defined in <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              href="23.301.dita#FAR_23_301"
                              base="FAR-23.301"
                              xtrc="23.301"
                              class="- topic/xref ">23.301</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1550e22">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> If the contract is awarded by an agency other than the Department of Defense, the contracting officer shall use the clause at <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              href="52.223-3.dita#FAR_52_223_3"
                              base="FAR-52.223-3"
                              xtrc="52.223-3"
                              class="- topic/xref "/> with its <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate I.</i>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1550e29">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        href="52.223-7.dita#FAR_52_223_7"
                        base="FAR-52.223-7"
                        xtrc="52.223-7"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>, Notice of Radioactive Materials, in solicitations and contracts for supplies that are or that containâ€”</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1550e35">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Radioactive material requiring specific licensing under regulations issued pursuant to the Atomic Energy Act of 1954; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1550e40">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Radioactive material not requiring specific licensing in which the specific activity is greater than 0.002 microcuries per gram or the activity per item equals or exceeds 0.01 microcuries. Such supplies include, but are not limited to, aircraft, ammunition, missiles, vehicles, electronic tubes, instrument panel gauges, compasses, and identification markers.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
